                    <h2>Manchester Town Hall</h2>
                    <p>Manchester Town Hall is a Gothic-style building constructed in the 19th century, located in Albert Square. This building serves not only as the town hall but also as an important symbol of the city. The exterior is magnificent, and the interior is beautifully decorated, especially with murals that depict Manchester's history during the Industrial Revolution. The town hall is often used as a filming location for movies and television shows, making it a must-see landmark for visitors.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="attraction">
                <img src="/images/location3.jpg" alt="Science and Industry Museum">
                <div>
                    <h2>Science and Industry Museum</h2>
                    <p>This museum is located in Manchester's historic industrial district and showcases the city's key role in the Industrial Revolution. The museum exhibits cover various fields including science, technology, and transportation, and it is home to one of the oldest railway stations in the world. It is not only a great place for family visits but also an ideal spot to explore Manchester's industrial heritage.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="attraction">
                <img src="/images/location4.jpg" alt="Old Trafford Stadium">
                <div>
                    <h2>Old Trafford Stadium</h2>
                    <p>Old Trafford is the home ground of Manchester United Football Club and is one of the most famous football stadiums in the world. This stadium attracts not only football fans but also sports enthusiasts. The venue includes a museum and guided tours, offering visitors an in-depth look at the stadium's history, the stories of the players, and the football culture behind it.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
